Chapter: CDX Binary Format Writer

 Produces CDX1 binaries per the Codex Binary specification. CDX is the
 native binary format for Codex.OS. Unlike ELF, it carries trust metadata
 in the header: author identity, cryptographic signature, a capability
 manifest, and proof hashes. The loader verifies all of this before
 mapping a single byte of code.

 During development the crypto fields are zero-filled because the
 SHA-256 and Ed25519 primitives are post-MM4 dependencies. The structural
 layout is production-final; only the zero bytes change when crypto
 arrives. See docs/Codex.OS/CodexBinary.md for the full format spec
 and docs/Codex.OS/CdxPhase2Notes.md for development-mode rationale.

 Uses write-i16, write-i32, write-i64, write-bytes from the encoder
 and pad-zeros from the ELF writer.

Section: CDX Format Constants

  cdx-magic : List Integer
  cdx-magic =
   [67, 68, 88, 49]

  cdx-format-version : Integer
  cdx-format-version =
   1

  cdx-fixed-header-size : Integer
  cdx-fixed-header-size =
   224

  cdx-content-hash-size : Integer
  cdx-content-hash-size =
   32

  cdx-author-key-size : Integer
  cdx-author-key-size =
   32

  cdx-signature-size : Integer
  cdx-signature-size =
   64

Section: CDX Flags

  cdx-flag-bare-metal : Integer
  cdx-flag-bare-metal =
   1

  cdx-flag-needs-heap : Integer
  cdx-flag-needs-heap =
   2

  cdx-flag-needs-stack-guard : Integer
  cdx-flag-needs-stack-guard =
   4

  cdx-flag-has-proofs : Integer
  cdx-flag-has-proofs =
   8

Section: CDX Header

  cdx-header-bytes : Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> List Integer
  cdx-header-bytes (flags) (cap-off) (cap-sz) (proof-off) (proof-sz) (text-off) (text-sz) (rodata-off) (rodata-sz) (entry) (stack-sz) (heap-sz) =
   cdx-magic
   ++ write-i16 cdx-format-version
   ++ write-i16 flags
   ++ pad-zeros cdx-content-hash-size
   ++ pad-zeros cdx-author-key-size
   ++ pad-zeros cdx-signature-size
   ++ write-i64 cap-off
   ++ write-i64 cap-sz
   ++ write-i64 proof-off
   ++ write-i64 proof-sz
   ++ write-i64 text-off
   ++ write-i64 text-sz
   ++ write-i64 rodata-off
   ++ write-i64 rodata-sz
   ++ write-i64 entry
   ++ write-i32 stack-sz
   ++ write-i32 heap-sz
   ++ write-i16 0
   ++ write-i16 0
   ++ write-i32 0

Section: CDX Binary Builder

  build-cdx : Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> List Integer -> List Integer -> List Integer
  build-cdx (flags) (entry-offset) (stack-size) (heap-size) (text) (rodata) =
   let hdr = cdx-fixed-header-size
   in let text-size = list-length text
   in let rodata-size = list-length rodata
   in cdx-header-bytes flags hdr 0 hdr 0 hdr text-size (hdr + text-size) rodata-size entry-offset stack-size heap-size
   ++ text
   ++ rodata

  build-cdx-bare-metal : Integer -> Integer -> Integer -> List Integer -> List Integer -> List Integer
  build-cdx-bare-metal (entry-offset) (stack-size) (heap-size) (text) (rodata) =
   build-cdx (cdx-flag-bare-metal + cdx-flag-needs-heap) entry-offset stack-size heap-size text rodata

